This top-level package diagram captures the significant packages, diagrams, and blocks of the factory work-cell.

The Factory Workcell package contains block, interfaces, and constraints used to build realizable models of factory workcells in which wireless networks are used for sensing and control of factory operation.
The General package contains components related to the functionality that may be applicable to all devices. It includes reusable constraints and components such as clocks.
The Motion Constraints package contains constraint blocks related to general linear motion.
The Time package contains constraint blocks related to time, clocks, and clock performance.
The Radio Constraints package contains constraint blocks related to radio wave propagation.
The Data Constraints package contains constraint blocks related to network performance.
The Network package contains components related to the functionality of industrial wireless networks used in factories.
The Wireless Device package contains components related to the functionality of Wireless Devices.
The Spectrum Monitoring System (SMS) package contains components related to the functionality of industrial spectrum monitoring systems.
The HMI package contains components related to the functionality of human machine interfaces.
The Human package contains components related to the features and relationships of human beings existing in the work-cell.
The Vision package contains components related to the functionality of vision systems within the factory workcell.

Conceptual top-level block representing the work-cell. This block should be used as a guide for realizations of factory models. The Workcell block may be extended, but users should be aware that extraneous part properties will be present.
The CNC package contains components related to the functionality of Computer Numerically Controlled devices.
The PLC package contains components related to the functionality of supervisory control devices.
The Devices package contains components related to the functionality of general computational Devices.
The Wireless Device package contains components related to the functionality of Wireless Devices.
The Robotics package contains components related to the functionality of robots and their controllers.
The Application package contains components representing the functionality of Devices.
The Conceptual Examples package provide examples of how to use the modeling elements of the Factory Workcell package.
This example shows two robots collaborating in a pick and place work-cell operation. The work-cell includes discrete I/O which is also wireless. The IWN is depicted with parametric constraints.

mdElement.text: The Workcell block is purely conceptual. Realization using the blocks within this model should be created using a new block not defined within this model. Examples include the Industrial Wireless Systems Testbed (IWS_Testbed) package included within this project.
